1. pre-commit — Runs before a commit is created
================
Use it to lint code, run tests, or check formatting.
-in below script,avoid to commit a file with white space in every line of code

# .git/hooks/pre-commit
# make a script with tail white space and without whitespace
#!/bin/sh

echo "Running pre-commit checks..."

# Example: Prevent committing if there are trailing whitespaces
if grep -rn " $" --include="*.js" .; then
  echo "❌ Error: Trailing whitespace found. Fix before committing."
  exit 1  # Non-zero exit cancels the commit
fi

echo "✅ Pre-commit checks passed."
exit 0

2. commit-msg: — Validates the commit message
===============
Enforce conventions like Conventional Commits or ticket numbers.
# .git/hooks/commit-msg
# git commit -m "feat: new update" ✅.but "feat: new update"❌
#!/bin/sh

COMMIT_MSG_FILE=$1
COMMIT_MSG=$(cat "$COMMIT_MSG_FILE")

# Example: Enforce format like "feat: add login page" or "fix: null pointer"
PATTERN="^(feat|fix|docs|style|refactor|test|chore): .+"

if ! echo "$COMMIT_MSG" | grep -qE "$PATTERN"; then
  echo "❌ Bad commit message: '$COMMIT_MSG'"
  echo "   Format must be: <type>: <description>"
  echo "   Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore"
  exit 1
fi

echo "✅ Commit message is valid."
exit 0


3. pre-push — Runs before pushing to remote
==============
Good for running full test suites before code reaches the server.
#create file.js
# .git/hooks/pre-push
#!/bin/sh

echo "Running tests before push..."

# Example: Run npm tests and block push if they fail
npm init -y
npm test

if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
  echo "❌ Tests failed. Push aborted."
  exit 1
fi

echo "✅ All tests passed. Pushing..."
exit 0

4. post-commit — Runs after a commit is made
=================
The post-commit hook runs after a commit is successfully created, typically for logging, notifications, or non-critical follow-up tasks.
Useful for notifications or logging (can't cancel the commit).
# .git/hooks/post-commit
#!/bin/sh

# Example: Log commit info to a file
COMMIT_HASH=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD)
COMMIT_MSG=$(git log -1 --pretty=%B)
echo "[$( date )] $COMMIT_HASH - $COMMIT_MSG" >> ~/commit-log.txt

echo "📝 Commit logged."


5. pre-merge-commit — Runs before a merge commit
==========================
Prevents problematic or unauthorized merges before the merge commit is created, enforcing team workflows and branch protection rules.
Prevent merging branches that don't meet standards.
# .git/hooks/pre-merge-commit
#!/bin/sh

echo "Checking branch before merge..."

BRANCH=$(git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD)

# Example: Block merging directly into main
if [ "$BRANCH" = "main" ]; then
  echo "❌ Direct merges into 'main' are not allowed. Use a PR."
  exit 1
fi

exit 0








